# Introduction

## Data

For this analysis we'll use the `penguins` dataset from the [**palmerpenguins**](https://allisonhorst.github.io/palmerpenguins/ "Link to palmerpenguins documentation") package.[@gorman2014]



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(tidyverse)
library(ggthemes)
library(palmerpenguins)
library(gt)
```
:::



## Species

@fig-bill-dims-species is a bar plot of species of penguins.



::: {.cell output-location='column-fragment' fig.asp='0.618'}

```{.r .cell-code  code-line-numbers="|2|3-6|10"}
ggplot(
  penguins,
  aes(
    x = bill_length_mm, y = bill_depth_mm,
    color = species, shape = species
  )
) +
  geom_point() +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_colorblind() +
  labs(x = "Bill length (mm)", y = "Bill depth (mm)")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![A scatterplot of three species of penguins showing the relationship between
bill depth and bill length.
](index_files/figure-pdf/fig-bill-dims-species-1.pdf){#fig-bill-dims-species fig-pos='H' fig-alt='A scatterplot of three species of penguins showing the relationship between
bill depth and bill length.
'}
:::
:::



## Penguins

@tbl-penguins-top10 shows the first 10 penguins from the dataset.



::: {#tbl-penguins-top10 .cell tbl-cap='Top 10 rows of the penguins dataset.'}

```{.r .cell-code}
penguins |>
  slice_head(n = 10) |>
  select(species, island, bill_length_mm, bill_depth_mm) |>
  gt()
```
